<subSubSection id="C3636562B7358F2AFF4AFE02FE0EFE08" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC636E9B7358F2AFF4AFE02FE0EFE08" blockId="41.[151,1436,151,536]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90DEAFBB7358F2AFF4AFE02FE9FFE50" bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective, “ 
<emphasis id="B90DEAFBB7358F2AFD0BFE02FD18FE50" box="[646,713,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">brevis</emphasis>
”, meaning short, and the adjective “ 
<emphasis id="B90DEAFBB7358F2AFBEBFE02FB64FE50" box="[1126,1205,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">pilosus</emphasis>
”, covered with hair, in reference to the conspicuous eye hairs that appear to be slightly shorter than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D6AB7358F2AFB30FE2FFA91FE2D" box="[1213,1344,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Houghia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurifera">
<emphasis id="B90DEAFBB7358F2AFB30FE2FFA91FE2D" box="[1213,1344,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. aurifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C794D6AB7358F2AFA0CFE2FFEC4FE08" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Houghia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipilosa">
<emphasis id="B90DEAFBB7358F2AFA0CFE2FFEC4FE08" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">H. longipilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
